  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Possible felony charges\n- Significant prison time (often several years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset seizure\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Personal consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential immigration issues\n\nThe specific penalties depend on the amount of money involved, the jurisdiction, and individual circumstances. Prosecution typically involves law enforcement agencies like the FBI and Department of Justice.",
